If we can do this, Khan added, the citizens will feel more comfortable.
The research into this technology has led some state agencies to call on a small California startup called True Mileage.
Originally, the company was not intended to help motorists who pay taxes to the states.
She was trying to break into the emerging auto insurance market, where drivers would pay based on their mileage.
