The new nicotine vaccine could suppress the pleasure of smoking
Scientists have developed a nicotine-resistant vaccine that could suppress the pleasure of smoking.
A single dose of the vaccine could protect mice from nicotine addiction for life.
Further tests are needed before human trials begin, but Professor Ronald Crystal of Weill Cornell Medical College in New York said the first signs were encouraging.
 We really hope that this kind of vaccine strategy will help millions of smokers who have tried to quit, exhausting all the methods available on the market today, but find that their addiction is strong enough to overcome these different approaches , said Professor Cornell.
The new vaccine contains a harmless virus that has been modified to carry the genetic information needed to design nicotine-resistant antibodies.
The virus selectively infects the liver cells, which then begin to produce a regular flow of antibodies.
The antibodies track all the nicotine molecules in the blood system and neutralize them before they reach the brain, preventing the smoker from getting his dose of nicotine.
During the tests, the vaccinated mice who were then given nicotine continued their normal activity.
But the mice that had not been vaccinated were calmed down, the researchers said, a sign that nicotine had reached their brains.
The experiments are described in the journal Science Translational Medicine.
Previous vaccines against tobacco use have proven ineffective because they contained antibodies.
Injections had to be repeated so frequently that antibody levels remained high that they were too expensive and impractical.
But the cost of the new vaccine should be much lower because it turns liver cells into antibody plants.
Professor Crystal said that if the future human vaccine was completely safe, it could be given to children before they are tempted to try a cigarette, which would prevent any nicotine addiction.
But it's more likely to be used by smokers who want to quit.
 They will know that if they start smoking again, they will not enjoy it because of the nicotine vaccine, and this may help them to lose their bad habit , he added.
