Passengers will have to put their smartphones, tablets and other devices on air.
So still not Words With Friends, the online game of Scrabble style that actor Alec Baldwin played on his smartphone in 2011 when he was loudly kicked out of an American Airlines plane after refusing to turn off his device while it was parked at the door.
And heavier devices like laptops will always have to be stored because they could hurt someone if they were to fly through the cabin.
Mobile phones on board will also continue to be banned.
The regulatory power for mobile phones is the Federal Communications Commission and not the FAA.
