Living together in French, the challenge of the Marguerite-Bourgeoys school board
In the Marguerite-Bourgeoys school board, 62% of pupils have a native language other than French.
This has prompted a consultation with parents, students, teachers and education staff about ways to better integrate students living on horseback across cultures.
The school board has just unveiled its vision of "Living together in French".
The organisation Vision Diversity has been running for a year in schools to help students from all backgrounds discover common landmarks that are not limited to the French language.
